-- Shares of Brazil retailer B2W soar on Tiger Global investment
-- By Asher Levine
-- Mon Jan 27, 2014 07:48AM EST
-- None



SAO PAULO, Jan 27 (Reuters) - Shares of Brazil's B2W Companhia Digital <BTOW3.SA> posted their biggest one-day gain ever on Monday after the online retailer said Tiger Global Management LLC might spend up to 1.2 billion reais ($500 million) to buy a stake.

Brazilian retailer Lojas Americanas SA <LAME4.SA>, B2W's largest shareholder, with a 62.2 percent stake, and two funds overseen by Tiger Global will jointly inject 2.38 billion reais into B2W, according to a securities filing late Friday. [ID:nL2N0L008V] At 10:40 a.m. (1240 GMT), B2W shares were up 30.3 percent at 20.20 reais.